<subSubSection id="C30D654BFFBFFF9B9A53FBCDF9B23508" pageId="46" pageNumber="47" type="description">
<paragraph id="8BA836C0FFBFFF9B9A53FBCDF9B23508" blockId="46.[151,1437,151,1977]" pageId="46" pageNumber="47">
<emphasis id="B963EAD2FFBFFF9B9A53FBCDF912345D" bold="true" box="[558,851,1086,1113]" pageId="46" pageNumber="47">Northern Smoothtongue</emphasis>
. To 
<quantity id="4CEF9B25FFBFFF9B9BFBFBCDF98D345C" box="[902,972,1087,1113]" metricMagnitude="-1" metricUnit="m" metricValue="2.0" pageId="46" pageNumber="47" unit="cm" value="20.0">20 cm</quantity>
(
<quantity id="4CEF9B25FFBFFF9B9BA0FBCDFE61345F" box="[989,1056,1087,1114]" metricMagnitude="-1" metricUnit="m" metricValue="2.0066" pageId="46" pageNumber="47" unit="in" value="7.9">7.9 in</quantity>
) SL or more (
<bibRefCitation id="EF864B31FFBFFF9B9CBDFBCDFB433478" author="Mason and Phillips" firstAuthor="Mason" pageId="46" pageNumber="47" pagination="1144 - 1153" refId="ref299242" refString="Mason, J. C. &amp; Phillips, A. C. 1985. Biology of the bathylagid fish, Leuroglossus schmidti, in the Strait of Georgia, British Columbia, Canada. Canadian Journal of Fisheries and Aquatic Sciences, 42, 1144 - 1153." type="journal article" year="1985">Mason and Phillips 1985</bibRefCitation>
). Northern Honshu, 
<collectingCountry id="F3007650FFBFFF9B999AFB91F8663478" box="[487,551,1123,1149]" name="Japan" pageId="46" pageNumber="47">Japan</collectingCountry>
to Sea of Okhotsk to Bering Sea (Mecklenburg 
<emphasis id="B963EAD2FFBFFF9B9C39FB91FE3D3478" box="[1092,1148,1123,1149]" italics="true" pageId="46" pageNumber="47">et al.</emphasis>
2002) to southern British Columbia (
<bibRefCitation id="EF864B31FFBFFF9B993BFB75FB9234A4" author="Peden, A. E." box="[326,467,1159,1185]" pageId="46" pageNumber="47" pagination="2396 - 2398" refId="ref310947" refString="Peden, A. E. (1981) Recognition of Leuroglossus schmidti and L. stilbius (Bathylagidae, Pisces) as distinct species in the North Pacific Ocean. Canadian Journal of Zoology, 59, 2396 - 2398." type="journal article" year="1981">Peden 1981</bibRefCitation>
). Adults primarily epipelagic to upper mesopelagic; depth: near surface to 
<quantity id="4CEF9B25FFBFFF9B9D40FB75FFDD34A4" box="[1341,1436,1159,1185]" metricMagnitude="3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.8" pageId="46" pageNumber="47" unit="m" value="1800.0">1,800 m</quantity>
(
<quantity id="4CEF9B25FFBFFF9B98B3FB58FB6834C3" box="[206,297,1194,1222]" metricMagnitude="3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.7998439999999998" pageId="46" pageNumber="47" unit="ft" value="5905.0">5,905 ft</quantity>
) (Mecklenburg 
<emphasis id="B963EAD2FFBFFF9B99A0FB59F85434C0" box="[477,533,1195,1221]" italics="true" pageId="46" pageNumber="47">et al.</emphasis>
2002). Classified in 
<taxonomicName id="4C174D43FFBFFF9B9B7CFB59F93E34C0" authorityName="Gunther" authorityYear="1878" box="[769,895,1195,1221]" class="Actinopterygii" family="Bathylagidae" genus="Bathylagus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Osmeriformes" pageId="46" pageNumber="47" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B963EAD2FFBFFF9B9B7CFB59F93E34C0" box="[769,895,1195,1221]" italics="true" pageId="46" pageNumber="47">Bathylagus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
by some authors. Records from south of British Columbia (e.g., 
<bibRefCitation id="EF864B31FFBFFF9B9906FB3DF84F34EC" author="Lauth" box="[379,526,1231,1257]" firstAuthor="Lauth" pageId="46" pageNumber="47" refId="ref294245" refString="Lauth, R. R. (1999) The 1997 Pacific Coast West Coast upper continental slope trawl survey of groundfish resources off Washington, Oregon, and California: estimates of distribution, abundance, and length composition. National Marine Fisheries Service Technical Memorandum, NMFS-AFSC- 97." type="journal volume" year="1999">Lauth (1999)</bibRefCitation>
from Point Conception, California) likely relate to 
<taxonomicName id="4C174D43FFBFFF9B9C33FB3DFEFD34EC" authorityName="Gilbert" authorityYear="1890" box="[1102,1212,1231,1257]" class="Actinopterygii" family="Bathylagidae" genus="Leuroglossus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Osmeriformes" pageId="46" pageNumber="47" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="stilbius">
<emphasis id="B963EAD2FFBFFF9B9C33FB3DFEFD34EC" box="[1102,1212,1231,1257]" italics="true" pageId="46" pageNumber="47">L. stilbius</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(
<bibRefCitation id="EF864B31FFBFFF9B9CB6FB3DFF1334EC" author="Peden, A. E." box="[1227,1362,1231,1257]" pageId="46" pageNumber="47" pagination="2396 - 2398" refId="ref310947" refString="Peden, A. E. (1981) Recognition of Leuroglossus schmidti and L. stilbius (Bathylagidae, Pisces) as distinct species in the North Pacific Ocean. Canadian Journal of Zoology, 59, 2396 - 2398." type="journal article" year="1981">Peden 1981</bibRefCitation>
, Dunn 1983; nomenclatural history is summarized in Mecklenburg 
<emphasis id="B963EAD2FFBFFF9B9B16FB01F9E23508" box="[875,931,1267,1293]" italics="true" pageId="46" pageNumber="47">et al.</emphasis>
2002).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
